0018|- [HelpText]
0019|*A control line (with a '-' in the control column) in the print list
0020|*and having the form
0021|*  - include <text_file>
S   |             <         >
0022|*specifies lines of a text file to be included as control lines.
0023|*The default directory for <text_file> is the current data directory
S   |                           <         >
0024|*and secondarily, <Survo>\U\SYS on the system disk.
S   |                  <     >
0025|*There is no default extension in the file name, but .DEV is recommended
0026|*for proper device drivers.
0028|*<text_file> usually contains define and shadow lines which describe
S   | <         >
0029|*the features of the current printer for the PRINT program. Such a
0030|*text file can be considered a device driver, since all the information
0031|*about the printer has to be supplied by means of a series of - define,
0032|*- shadow, and other control lines.
0034|*The system file SURVO.APU defines the default device driver for
0035|Sprinting as print_dev=PS.DEV (for example) and then the lines
S   |             7777777777777777
0036|*of the text file (device driver) PS.DEV are processed by the PRINT
0037|*operation as control lines before processing of lines in the print list.
0038|*Thus the task of the driver file is to teach the PRINT program all the
0039|*control words and codes of the current printer.
0040|*The default device driver is replaced by another by using a control line
0041|*of the form
0042|*  - include <text_file.DEV>
S   |             <             >
0043|Sas the first line (L1) in the print list of PRINT L1,L2.
S   |        44444
0045|*The features described in device drivers are usually activated by
0046|*control lines of the form
0047|* - [word1][word2][word3]
0048|*where strings in brackets are control words and macros defined
0049|*by - define lines in the print list or in include files (drivers).
0050|*For example,
0051|* - [Times(12)][line_spacing(14)]
0052|*selects (according to PS.DEV) the 12 point Times-Roman font ([Times(12)])
0053|*and line spacing of 14 points ([line_spacing(14)]).
0055|*The user can make new device drivers for various printers by using any
0056|*existing Survo printer driver as a model or the user may modify and
0057|*enlarge the existing ones. For example, all the control words can be
0058|*translated to another language.
0060|*Please, note also that by referring to additional include files (for logos,
0061|*etc.) in the print list, the user can easily enter various enhancements
0062|*without the need to rewrite them completely.
