0070|- [HelpText]
0071|*A control line (with a '-' in the control column) in the print list
0072|*or in an include file (driver) and having the form
0073|*  - define [new_word] [word1][word2]...
0074|*defines a new control word [new_word] as a combination (concatenation)
0075|*of previously defined words [word1][word2]...
0076|*The only predefined 'words' are the characters and character codes
0077|*in hexadecimal form in brackets. Thus [a/b] corresponds to decimal
0078|*code 16*a+b. All other words must be composed from characters and
0079|*from words already defined. Observe that any word can be redefined
0080|*later and all words depending on this word will be interpreted there-
0081|*after according to this new definition.
0082|*For example:
0083|*      - define [SP] [2/0]
0084|*      - define [three_spaces] [SP][SP][SP]
0085|*      - define [AA] A[three_spaces]A
0086|*Any control word thus defined can be used on a control line (having
0087|*a '-' in the control column). For example line
0088|*      - [AA][SP][AA]
0089|*will produce same output as a normal edit line
0090|*      *A   A A   A
0092|*The maximum amount of text in control word definitions of PRINT
0093|*is by default limited to 60000 bytes.
0094|*This value can be altered by giving a line
0095|*    printdef=<size>
S   |              <    >
0096|*in the control file SURVO.APU.
