0104|- [HelpText]
0105|*A control line (with a '-' in the control column) in the print list
0106|*or in an include file (driver) and having the form
0107|*  - shadow <shadow_character>: [pre_code] [post_code]
S   |            <                >
0108|*where [pre_code] and (optional) [post_code] are defined earlier
0109|*defines the function of the <character> of the shadow line in the PRINT
S   |                             <         >
0110|*operation.
0111|*Thus when printing a character, say A, having <shadow_character> on
S   |                                               <                >
0112|*the shadow line, the following sequence will be printed:
0113|*      [pre_code]A[post_code]
0114|*For example, the subscripts may be printed by defining '2' (which is
0115|*the standard attribute for subscripts) as a shadow character as
0116|*  - shadow 2: [INDEX][half_line_down] [MAIN][half_line_up]
0117|*provided that the control words appearing in the definition are
0118|*properly specified earlier.
